Items recovered from the suspected bandits on August 24, 2021. [Standard]  Police on Tuesday, August 24 shot dead two suspected bandits in Habaswein Sub-County in Wajir County.  In a report filed at the Habaswein Police Station under the OB Number 06/24/08/2021, the suspected bandits were gunned down at Dadaber area at 10:30am after allegedly refusing to heed surrender orders.  Police say the suspected bandits were “heavily armed”.  “A shoot-out, consequently, ensued and two bandits were fatally injured,” says the police report.  Kainuk town begins to rise from the ruins of banditry  Two ‘bright’ varsity students among the four killed by bandits  Bandits kill at least 20 in northwest Nigeria's Katsina state, say police  Armed bandits kill at least 18 in Nigeria's Katsina state One of the deceased has been identified as Police Constable Yerrow Noor from Dadaab. The other one remains unidentified.  Four AK-47 rifles, 316 bullets, empty magazines of AK-47 rifle, three KDF jackets, a smartphone and two feature phones were recovered from the deceased.  Their bodies were moved to a morgue in Wajir.   Tension high in Loosuk village Samburu county as 10 armed bandits invaded grazing livesto  Kijana wa umri wa miaka nane afungwa chini ya mti Pokot  Hospitali ya Kapenguria inapokea watoto zaidi ya sabini walioathirika na utapia mlo By Ali Abdi | 2 days ago By Ali Abdi | 2 days ago By Kamau Muthoni and Abdimalik Hajir | 12 days ago By Abdimalik Hajir | 22 days ago